<div id="helpHeader" class="m-b-xxxlg">
    <h3>How to use Sphere</h3>
    <p>Sphere is a personal relationship manager made for everyday life. Our mission is to make sure you never let a new or existing person in your life slip through the cracks.</p>
    <p>Your relationships will exist within Sphere in varying shapes and distance from your center bubble, kind of how you would visualize your social circle in real life. The size and shape of overall Sphere you’ll have will depend on how you use this app.</p>
</div>
<div class="container textLeft">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
            <h3 class="m-b-lg">Getting Started</h3>
            <!-- <div class="container"> -->
                <div class="row m-b-xxxlg">
                    <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3">
                        <%= image_tag "add-to-sphere", width:"80%" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9 textLeft">
                        Add connections (import from Google or manually) to start tracking your activities with them                   
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row m-b-xxxlg">
                    <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3">
                        Placeholder
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9 textLeft">
                        Clicking on your connection bubbles lets you check-in, book hangouts, and update their info. Check-ins and hangouts are logged for you for social points!
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row m-b-xxxlg">
                    <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3">
                        <%= image_tag "settings", width:"80%" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9 textLeft">
                        <p>Change the app defaults settings</p>
                        <p>View & restore any expired contacts</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            <!-- </div> -->
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
            <h3 class="m-b-lg">What do the icons mean?</h3>
            <!-- <div class="container"> -->
                <div class="row m-b-xxxlg">
                    <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3">
                        <%= image_tag "plans-small", width:"100%" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9 textLeft">
                        <p>The orange calendar indicates you’ve made plans with a contact. Plans can be made be clicking on your contacts bubble. Sphere will add the plans to your Google Calendar and you even have the option to send your friend an invite.</p>
                        <p>All plans and events you create will then be viewable in the Progress page and earn you social points.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row m-b-xxxlg">
                    <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3">
                        <%= image_tag "checked-in-small", width:"100%" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9 textLeft">
                        <p>The green check mark Indicates you’ve caught up with a contact, whether in person or otherwise. This will add points towards your relationship and your overall social score.</p>
                        <p>The more often you check-in with someone the larger their face grows, and the closer they get to your center.</p>
                        <p>Checking in with a friend resets their timer until your next hangout.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row m-b-xxxlg">
                    <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-2 col-xs-3">
                        <%= image_tag "expiring-small", width:"100%" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-10 col-md-10 col-sm-10 col-xs-9 textLeft">
                        <p>The red circle means it has been a while since you’ve checked in with a friend! Sphere will show how much time you have left to reach out.</p>
                        <p>If you ignore the time, the contact will expire out of your Sphere.</p>
                        <p>Users can restore expired connections in the Settings window while incurring a small points penalty.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            <!-- </div> -->
        </div>
    </div>
</div>